Futility

Move him into the sun—
Gently its touch awoke him once,
At home, whispering in the traumas...

We all pine for beauty, all turning to glow...
But nature lies now through war...
Let him dream under skies swarming with light...  
— Wilfred Owen

- Wilfred Owen
